That is safe in the face proxying. It is not safe in the face of dynamic subclassing, but i don&#39;t know of any EJB implementations that do that (although there are certainly JPA implementations which do that).

A slightly more complicated, but fundamentally more straightforward, implementation would be to define:

    public abstract String getSimpleClassName();

